OL,3,CTrain managers to strike for second
OL,4,Ctime in dispute over rest-day working
OL,6,FKathryn O'Brien, executive director of
OL,7,Fcustomer experience at Avanti West
OL,8,FCoast, said: "We're disappointed by
OL,9,Fthe RMT calling strike action on 2
OL,10,FJanuary. Our customers will face
OL,11,Fsignificantly disrupted journeys as a
OL,12,Fresult, and I would like to thank them
OL,13,Ffor their patience and understanding.
OL,15,F"On the strike day we'll have a
OL,16,Fsignificantly reduced service, so
OL,17,Fcustomers with tickets for January 2
OL,18,Fare strongly advised to travel on
OL,19,Falternative dates or claim a full fee-
OL,20,Ffree refund. We remain open to working
OL,21,Fwith the RMT to resolve the dispute."
